This paper is primarily focused on improving language modeling using deep neural networks, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of adversarial training, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of deep learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper presents a closed-form solution for the optimal adversarial noise, which involves mathematical optimization and could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the diversity of embedding vectors, which is a topic related to neural networks and could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper presents results on machine translation, which involves computer vision techniques and could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
